description:
What is physics good for? Well, according to theoretical physicist Michio Kaku, everything.  
From the early moments of the universe to the hunt for the Higgs Boson, the string theory specialist and prolific author provides a beautifully accessible explanation of why &quot;the history of physics is the history of modern civilization.&quot;

